{
  "stem": "18102.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Clearly had he been there, he would have been arrested, and this story would have been totally different.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So here was a turning point in our lives, the fact he had escaped, left, and never was there to be arrested.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It, it of course [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] wasn't the first turning point in this story, but it's clearly a critical juncture.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Germans [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] then were making a pact with Stalin.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Stalin and Hitler, the Russians and the Germans, made a pact, a non-aggression treaty.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the Russians bought time and Hitler, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for whatever political reasons, divided Poland with Stalin so that the part that was Bialystok would be turned over to the Russians, and the rest of Poland would be for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That meant that on a given day the Germans would march out, and the Russians would march in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it was a, a real festive kind of feeling because the, the real feared enemy was the Germans, much more so than the Russians, or at least it was felt that way.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the day that the Germans were marching out of the city was a-- somewhat of a celebratory day.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My mother took me to watch the scene where, in the big street-- middle of town, which was a divided thoroughfare with flowers in the middle and traffic going in one direction and the other side traffic going in the opposite direction, and in fact, the Germans marched out.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The, the, the throngs that came to witness the scene-- maybe it was half of Bialystok was there to witness the scene-- was quiet as the Germans marched out.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was hardly a sound.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
